isfaction. At the heart of the UX process is the most important stakeholder - the user. This book will help you create the business case, education, processes, skills, tools, and the philosophy to deliver effective and enjoyable user experiences. These in turn will drive success in the modern software-enabled organization. Includes key considerations for creating a business case for UX within their organization and engaging senior business roles around the necessary business change required.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aGedrange. 4aGeschaft. 4aInformationstechnologie. 4aSoftware-Entwicklung. 4aUX-Design. 7aCOMPUTERS / General.2bisacsh  auser experience, industrial engineering, computer science, technology projects, design, software-enabled organization, iterative UX process.1 aBaines, Jeremy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131912408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023z9783111318165oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI AI COLLECTIONz978311157353308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024z978311156434008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI and ITGP STEM IT PACKAGEz978311157407308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97815015180580 cprintz978150152152240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151804140uhttps://www.degruyter